<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="5" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1437,394,743]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,273,394,419]" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Diagnosis.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName box="[282,365,396,419]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Thygater" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anae">
<emphasis box="[282,365,396,419]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. anae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is sympatric and similar to 
<taxonomicName box="[686,784,394,419]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Macrocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis box="[686,784,394,419]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. analis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[842,998,394,419]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Thygater" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palliventris">
<emphasis box="[842,998,394,419]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. palliventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. Females of all these species have the apical stripe of disc and apical margin of terga translucent-amber and in all of them males may have entirely-black integument with head and mesossomal pilosity predominantly whitish. The females of 
<taxonomicName box="[1120,1201,468,491]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Thygater" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anae">
<emphasis box="[1120,1201,468,491]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. anae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can be distinguished from females of 
<taxonomicName box="[339,436,502,527]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Macrocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis box="[339,436,502,527]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. analis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
for the metasomal pilosity (completely yellowish in 
<taxonomicName box="[1035,1117,503,526]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Thygater" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anae">
<emphasis box="[1035,1117,503,526]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. anae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
— 
<figureCitation box="[1148,1213,502,527]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,961,983]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,940]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,940]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. T. anae — ♀: A — frontal view, B — lateral view, C — dorsal view (DZUP Santa Tereza—ES, Brasil, 8 / 11 / 1967, C. T. &amp; C. Elias lg, Paratype); ♂: D — frontal view, E — lateral view, F — dorsal view (UFMG 1200097). Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/344985/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
.A, B, C, and bright yellow on marginal zones of T2–T4 of 
<taxonomicName box="[605,703,538,563]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Macrocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis box="[605,703,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. analis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
— 
<figureCitation box="[734,799,538,563]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1800,1822]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1064,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,1064,1779]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. T. analis — ♀: A — frontal view, B — lateral view, C — dorsal view (UFMG 34096); ♂: D — frontal view, E — lateral view, F — dorsal view, G — Genital capsule (the arrow indicates the long projection on the anterior margin of the spata, mentioned in couplet 7 of the key to males) (UFMG 1402951). Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/344986/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
.C) and for the clypeal punctation (sparse,&gt; 1 
<emphasis box="[1340,1374,538,563]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">dp,</emphasis>
in 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Thygater" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anae">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. anae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
— 
<figureCitation box="[235,304,574,599]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,961,983]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,940]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,940]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. T. anae — ♀: A — frontal view, B — lateral view, C — dorsal view (DZUP Santa Tereza—ES, Brasil, 8 / 11 / 1967, C. T. &amp; C. Elias lg, Paratype); ♂: D — frontal view, E — lateral view, F — dorsal view (UFMG 1200097). Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/344985/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
.A; dense, &lt;1 
<emphasis box="[480,516,574,599]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">dp,</emphasis>
in 
<taxonomicName box="[558,658,574,599]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Macrocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis box="[558,658,574,599]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. analis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
— 
<figureCitation box="[688,756,574,599]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1800,1822]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,1064,1779]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,1064,1779]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 5. T. analis — ♀: A — frontal view, B — lateral view, C — dorsal view (UFMG 34096); ♂: D — frontal view, E — lateral view, F — dorsal view, G — Genital capsule (the arrow indicates the long projection on the anterior margin of the spata, mentioned in couplet 7 of the key to males) (UFMG 1402951). Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/344986/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 5</figureCitation>
.A). In female 
<taxonomicName box="[930,1089,574,599]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Thygater" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palliventris">
<emphasis box="[930,1089,574,599]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. palliventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the clypeus has a shiny midlongitudinal band and, in most specimens, a yellow, apical transverse stripe (
<figureCitation box="[1058,1144,610,635]" captionStart="FIGURE 12" captionStartId="19.[151,250,1244,1266]" captionTargetBox="[150,1436,445,1222]" captionTargetId="figure@19.[150,1436,445,1222]" captionTargetPageId="19" captionText="FIGURE 12. T. palliventris— ♀: A — frontal view, B — lateral view, C — dorsal view (UFMG 19324); ♂: D — frontal view, E — lateral view, F — dorsal view (UFMG 1602166). Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/344993/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 12</figureCitation>
.A), while in 
<taxonomicName box="[1304,1390,612,635]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Thygater" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anae">
<emphasis box="[1304,1390,612,635]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. anae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
the clypeus is homogeneously punctate and has no yellow stripe (
<figureCitation box="[858,928,646,671]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="8.[151,250,961,983]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,193,940]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[151,1436,193,940]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 4. T. anae — ♀: A — frontal view, B — lateral view, C — dorsal view (DZUP Santa Tereza—ES, Brasil, 8 / 11 / 1967, C. T. &amp; C. Elias lg, Paratype); ♂: D — frontal view, E — lateral view, F — dorsal view (UFMG 1200097). Scale bar = 1 mm." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/344985/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 4</figureCitation>
.A). Male 
<taxonomicName box="[1044,1127,647,670]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Thygater" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="anae">
<emphasis box="[1044,1127,647,670]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. anae</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are similar to males of the sympatric species 
<taxonomicName box="[359,456,682,707]" class="Insecta" family="Keroplatidae" genus="Macrocera" kingdom="Animalia" order="Diptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="analis">
<emphasis box="[359,456,682,707]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. analis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[513,669,682,707]" class="Insecta" family="Apidae" genus="Thygater" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="5" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="palliventris">
<emphasis box="[513,669,682,707]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">T. palliventris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but can be distinguished from them by the presence of a complete marginal fringe in S4 that is absent in the others two (
<figureCitation box="[752,817,718,743]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1416,1438]" captionTargetBox="[151,1436,796,1395]" captionTargetId="figure@4.[151,1436,796,1395]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. Ventral view of metasoma of males. A — Thygater anae, B — T. analis (the arrows indicate the alternative states of the marginal fringe of S 4, mentioned in couplet 4 of the key to males)." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/344982/files/figure.png" pageId="4" pageNumber="5">Fig. 1</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
